%% 9. REVIEWER TESTING GUIDE — Key paths to verify
%% ============================================================
%%
%% To test the application end-to-end:
%%
%% 1. SETUP
%%    mysql -u root -e "CREATE DATABASE writerassistant CHARACTER SET utf8mb4"
%%    npm install
%%    cp .env.example .env   (configure DATABASE_URL, SESSION_SECRET, LLM_PROVIDER, LLM_API_KEY)
%%    npx prisma migrate dev
%%    npm run add-admin admin@test.com Password123! Admin
%%    npm run dev
%%
%% 2. AUTH FLOW
%%    - Visit http://localhost:3000 → should redirect to /auth/login
%%    - Login with admin credentials → should reach /dashboard
%%    - Verify dashboard shows stats (0 books)
%%
%% 3. BOOK CREATION
%%    - Go to /dashboard/books → click "New Book"
%%    - Create manually OR import a .txt/.pdf/.docx file
%%    - Verify chapters and sections appear in editor
%%
%% 4. EDITING
%%    - Select a section → type text in TipTap editor
%%    - Wait 2s → verify auto-save (no explicit save button)
%%    - Change fonts in book details → verify editor updates
%%
%% 5. STORY CONTEXT ANALYSIS
%%    - After editing, check worker terminal output for processing logs
%%    - Query: SELECT status, COUNT(*) FROM SectionAnalysis GROUP BY status
%%    - After ~30s idle + worker cycle, sections should be "completed"
%%    - Verify Qdrant has vectors: curl http://localhost:6333/collections/story_context
%%
%% 6. KNOWLEDGE ASSISTANT
%%    - Open the floating panel in the editor (brain icon)
%%    - Test general query: "What is the Silk Road?" → should return structured facts
%%    - Repeat same query → should return instantly (cache hit)
%%    - Test book query: "Who are the characters in my book?" → should return extracted data
%%    - Verify evidence links navigate to correct sections
%%
%% 7. QUERY CLASSIFICATION
%%    - "my character Elena" → should classify as book mode
%%    - "history of medieval castles" → should classify as general mode
%%    - Verify mode badge appears and override buttons work
%%
%% 8. USER MANAGEMENT (admin only)
%%    - Navigate to /dashboard/users
%%    - Create a CREATOR user via CLI: npm run add-user writer@test.com Pass123! Writer
%%    - Verify user appears in list
%%    - Toggle user active/inactive, change role
%%
%% 9. EDGE CASES
%%    - Stop Docker (docker compose down) → verify app degrades gracefully
%%    - Submit empty section → should mark as non-narrative, not crash
%%    - Submit policy-violating query ("write me a scene") → should return refusal
%%    - Kill worker mid-processing → after restart, stuck sections should recover
